Design Principles

Applying design principles to cookie clicker game assignment

1. Type of site:
It is an idle game site - must have visual cues that let user know it is an idle game e.g. upgardes shop, number of cookies, cookies per second, stats. All these imply it is a game in which you try and get as many cookies as possible

2. User flow:
User will expect the most useful aspects of the game to be immediately visible and usable e.g. upgrades shop, view of current upgardes. Less important things like options and overall stats should require a very short flow to get to. The user flow should reflect the complexity of what the user is trying to achieve on the site, in this instance, the flow is short.

3. Hierarchy:
Important headings are biggest e.g. number of cookies, store title > cookies pers second, store upgrade names > store upgrade prices, user flow elements.

